&gt;    here is a brief description. I wont go into details to
&gt;    much as I assume you are not a member of either ryu.
&gt;
&gt;    kukishinden Ryu (KSDR) Kodachi has only 3 kata for the
&gt;    use of the kodachi. Once source I know may try to say
&gt;    there are a further 7 ura gata for these 3 omote gata,
&gt;    but i have seen a Kukishin ryu densho and no ura gata
&gt;    were listed in it.
&gt;
&gt;    In each one the attacker will come at you with a
&gt;    katana and he is trying to cut across at your torso.
&gt;    The reason for this is you are moving around him and
&gt;    you decide when to expose a weak point therefore
&gt;    making him attack the area you choose. Once he does in
&gt;    all three you rush in fast and thrust the kodachi into
&gt;    him.
&gt;
&gt;    In Hon Tai Yoshin Ryu (HYR), I have not studied. I
&gt;    have been shown the kata once and I have them on
&gt;    video. therefore cant describe them properly.
&gt;
&gt;    There are five omote kata and I am told maybe some ura
&gt;    gata (which I have not seen or know of). They like the
&gt;    Kuki kodachi involve thrusting and a few slashing such
&gt;    as to the neck or torso.
&gt;
&gt;    The HYR tend to sink lower in kamae than the KSDR.
&gt;
&gt;    However there is a historical link between the two
&gt;    ryu.
&gt;
&gt;    Kukishinden Ryu is really called Kukishinden Happo
&gt;    Biken, and originates from Kukishin ryu (main branch
&gt;    of that is now Kukishinden Tenshin Hyoho) This all
&gt;    originates from the Kuki family who are today still
&gt;    soke of the tenshin hyoho branch, and also head
&gt;    priests of the Kuki shrine. IN the 1600s Ohkuni Onihei
&gt;    was a shihan in the Kukishin ryu and met with Takagi
&gt;    Gennoshin from Takagi Yoshin ryu. together they
&gt;    exchanged ideas etc and Takagi Yoshin ryu was changed.
&gt;    Kukishin ryu Bojutsu was added to Takagi. In the early
&gt;    1900&#39;s Ishitani (Ishiya) sensei on his death bed
&gt;    handed menkyo kaiden makimono for the Takagi Yoshin
&gt;    ryu to Takamatsu Toshitsugu, they were to be passed to
&gt;    Kakuno one of his students. Both Kakuno and Takamatsu
&gt;    held menkyo Kaiden in Takagi Yoshin Ryu and kukishin
&gt;    Ryu. sort time later Minaki sensei is handed menkyo
&gt;    kaiden in the kakuno takagi ryu and from him him the
&gt;    HYR is developed.
&gt;
&gt;    for more indepth info and lines history check out
&gt;    these sites.
&gt;
&gt;    http://www.hontaiyoshinryu.com/
&gt;    http://www.hyrusa.com/index2.html
&gt;    http://www.shinjin.co.jp/kuki/hyoho/index_e.html
&gt;    http://kobe.cool.ne.jp/ikkansai/takagiryu.htm
&gt;    http://www.hanako.co.uk/History.htm  (my web site)
